    "Body": " Design Assurance Engineer - Limited Assignment - US Luminex - 3.5 Austin, TX Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $66,000 - $87,000 a year Qualifications Risk Management Writing Skills CGMP Time Management Usability Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description We envision a Luminex solution in every lab around the world seeking to obtain timely and confident answers. We aim to lead with transformative solutions that uniquely accelerate reliable answers while reducing the overall cost of advancing health. The Quality Assurance team is seeking candidates for an available Design Assurance Engineer position within the team. The selected candidate would be responsible for the following: Acting as the quality representative on design core teams for electromechanical instruments, reagents and assays for the life science and in-vitro diagnostics market Guiding the development teams through the Design Control process ensuring compliance with FDA, ISO, QSR, quality, safety and environmental regulations and internal procedures Providing provide support for quality initiatives, post market design changes/improvements and quality surveillance activities Key Responsibilities & Duties: Conflict Management\u2014settles disagreement and disputes equitably Learning on the Fly\u2014learns quickly/open to change Organizational Agility\u2014knows how to go through the proper channels to get things done Peer Relationship\u2014cooperative, team player, trusted and supported by peers Problem Solving\u2014 identifies complex problems and reviews related information to develop and evaluate options and implement solutions Timely Decision Making\u2014decisions can be made quickly even under tight deadlines and pressure Written Communications\u2014effectively communicates in writing Other duties as assigned. Education and Experience: Bachelor degree required, in a life science/engineering discipline required Experience in an Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) environment required, preferably in medical device industry Working knowledge of current industry quality practices under QSRs, ISO-13485 and international regulations Experience as a member of a design team preferred Minimum 5 years\u2019 experience in regulated environment required, previous design assurance experience preferred Experience with medical device risk management (ISO 14971) is preferred Experience with usability (ISO 62366) is preferred Training, Skills, and Certification/Licenses: Excellent interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills Certification in a quality discipline preferred, such as CQM, CQA, CQE, etc. Strong computer skills (Microsoft Windows and Office programs), familiarity with Oracle preferred High degree of problem solving and analytical skills Ability to apply statistical tools Strong organizational and time-management skills Work Condition: Must work onsite at Luminex office Travel may be required at least 20% of the time; internationally Possible exposure to Chemicals, Lasers, Excessive Noise, etc. Physical Demands: All positions require standing, stooping, bending, climbing, sitting, kneeling, and lifting at least 10 lbs. Luminex Corporation is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status of an otherwise qualified individual, citizenship status, membership or application for membership in a uniformed service, or any other protected characteristic or category protected by applicable law. "
